Customer Services Agent
Singapore Airlines
-
Houston, TX
Job Description
1. Check on pre-flight preparations for arrivals and departures.
2. Assist passengers on arrival at customers and immigration.
3. Supervise baggage handling to prevent mishandling.
4. Attend to all operational telexes.
5. Record statistical reports as required.
6. Perform arrival/departure/ramp duties.
7. Monitor handling agent at arrival, departure and boarding areas to ensure company's standards are met.
8 Assist with lost and found matters.
9. Follow-up on passenger's enquiries and feedback.
10. Participate in customer service improvement initiatives.
11. Other airport and administrative duties as assigned.
Qualifications
1. Ability to communicate well with traveling public and to be able to handle irate passengers effectviely.
2. Previous airport operations, ground service/passenger handling functions preferred but not essential.
3. Required to work shifts.
4. Overtime required for flight delays and through peak periods as necessary.
Additional Information
All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.
